<% content_for :title, "Community Guidelines" %>

<%= render layout: "pages/page_card", locals: { title: "Community Guidelines", subtitle: "Last updated: #{Date.today.strftime('%B %d, %Y')}" } do %>
  <section>
    <h2>Our community</h2>
    <p>
      Open Scene helps people discover and join local activities. These guidelines explain how we
      expect everyone to behave so the platform stays welcoming, safe, and useful for all members.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Be respectful</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Treat hosts, attendees, and other users with courtesy.</li>
      <li>Do not harass, threaten, or discriminate against anyone.</li>
      <li>Keep activity descriptions and messages appropriate for a diverse community.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Post honest, accurate activities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Use a clear title, date, location, and city so people know what they are joining.</li>
      <li>Set a realistic capacity when your venue or group has limits.</li>
      <li>Update or cancel activities if plans change so attendees are not misled.</li>
      <li>Only upload images you have the right to share and that relate to the activity.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Join and participate in good faith</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Sign up only for activities you intend to attend.</li>
      <li>Leave an activity if your plans change so a spot opens for someone else.</li>
      <li>Respect private events: use invite links only when the host shared them with you.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Keep the platform safe</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Do not spam, scrape, or automate signups or submissions.</li>
      <li>Do not attempt to access accounts, private activities, or admin features without permission.</li>
      <li>Report suspicious or harmful content to the team (see Contact below).</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Consequences</h2>
    <p>
      Content or behavior that violates these guidelines may be removed. Accounts may be suspended
      or deleted, especially for repeated or serious violations. See our
      <%= link_to "Terms of Service", terms_path %> for more detail.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions or concerns about community conduct? Contact a site administrator or report
      the issue to your activity host.
    </p>
  </section>
<% end %>
